# Deploy plan template

Filed per Trial 2 finding F4.10. Drop this into your project at
`docs/DEPLOY-PLAN.md` and customize for your hosting target.

Template covers Vercel + Supabase + Anthropic API (the validated TS/Next.js
adopter stack from temidev). Adapt the sections for other targets (Cloudflare
Pages · Netlify · Fly.io · self-hosted) — the discipline transfers.

---

## 1. Production environment matrix

| Env | URL | Branch | Supabase project | Anthropic API key env | Vault keys |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| **production** | `https://yourapp.com` | `main` | `prod-<slug>` | `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (prod) | `SUPABASE_VAULT_*_ID` (prod UUIDs) |
| **staging** | `https://staging.yourapp.com` | `staging` | `staging-<slug>` | `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (staging) | `SUPABASE_VAULT_*_ID` (staging UUIDs) |
| **preview** | `https://<pr-N>.yourapp-pr.vercel.app` | per-PR | shared with staging | shared with staging | shared with staging |

⚠ Preview envs share Supabase + Anthropic with staging by default. If you need
isolated preview DBs, use Supabase branches (Phase 2 trigger when team grows).

## 2. Vercel project configuration

### Initial setup
1. Create project in Vercel dashboard linked to GitHub repo
2. Framework preset: `Next.js`
3. Root directory: `/` (or your monorepo subpath)
4. Build command: `pnpm build` (or your equivalent)
5. Output directory: `.next` (Next.js default)

### Environment variables (Settings → Environment Variables)

| Variable | Scope | Source | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` | Production + Preview | Supabase project URL | Public · safe to expose |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | Production + Preview | Supabase anon key | Public · RLS protects |
| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | Production + Preview ⚠ | Supabase service role | **NEVER** put in `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` |
| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Production + Preview | Anthropic console | Server-only · NEVER prefix `NEXT_PUBLIC_` |
| `SUPABASE_VAULT_<DOMAIN>_KEY_ID` | Production + Preview | Provisioned per ADR-044 / 049 | UUID of Vault secret · NOT the secret itself |
| `RATE_LIMIT_IP_SALT` | Production + Preview | Random 32-char hex | For IP-hash anonymization (Sprint 023 pattern) |
| `<FEATURE>_ENABLED` | Production + Preview | `true` after VG passes | Global kill-switch · default false on first deploy |

⚠ `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` bypasses RLS. NEVER expose to client bundle.
Always import `createAdminClient()` from `lib/supabase/admin.ts` (server-only)
when service-role privilege is needed.

### Custom domain
1. Add domain in Settings → Domains
2. Configure DNS A/CNAME per Vercel instructions
3. Wait for SSL cert provisioning (~2-5 min)
4. Test redirects from `www.` to apex (or vice versa)

## 3. Supabase project configuration

### Initial setup
1. Create Supabase project at https://supabase.com/dashboard
2. Note the project URL + anon key + service role key
3. Enable Row Level Security on every table by default
4. Set up Auth providers (email · OAuth as needed)

### Vault secrets provisioning (for AI feature encryption)
Per `templates/SETUP-supabase.md.template`. Single key per encryption domain:
```bash
openssl rand -hex 32  # → 64 hex chars
```
1. Supabase Dashboard → Settings → Vault → New Secret
2. Name: descriptive (`agreement_signer_key` · `gcal_token_key`)
3. Paste hex value · copy UUID
4. Add UUID to Vercel env vars as `SUPABASE_VAULT_<DOMAIN>_KEY_ID`

### Migration push workflow

```bash
# Local: stage migration in supabase/migrations/<timestamp>_<slug>.sql
# Test idempotency:
supabase db reset --linked=false   # if Docker available
supabase db push --dry-run

# Push to remote at sprint close (deferred batch · per ADR-046 amendment):
supabase db push --include-all
supabase migration list   # verify zero local-only rows
```

## 4. Pre-launch checklist

### Code-side
- [ ] `pnpm type-check` clean
- [ ] `pnpm lint` clean
- [ ] `pnpm test` green (unit + integration)
- [ ] `pnpm test:e2e` green (Playwright · or your E2E suite)
- [ ] Security scan: `/security-review` skill session (or equivalent)
- [ ] All canonical artifacts up-to-date (HYPOTHESIS · RESPONSIBILITY-MAP · COST-BUDGET · etc.)

### Infrastructure
- [ ] Custom domain DNS configured + SSL cert active
- [ ] All env vars set in Vercel (Production + Preview scopes)
- [ ] Supabase RLS policies reviewed (no missing policies on user-facing tables)
- [ ] All migrations pushed to remote (`supabase migration list` shows zero drift)
- [ ] Vault keys provisioned for any encrypted-at-rest columns
- [ ] Rate-limit salt rotated from any committed default
- [ ] CORS allowlist matches the production domain

### Feature flags (per `/responsibility-map` kill-switch convention)
- [ ] All `<FEATURE>_ENABLED` env vars default to `false` on first deploy
- [ ] Enable after VG passes per feature
- [ ] Document the enable/disable runbook (≤30s recovery for incidents)

### Observability
- [ ] `/ai-observe` skill output emitted to logs (or your observability sink)
- [ ] Cost-budget alerts wired to your channel (Slack · email · PagerDuty)
- [ ] Audit log RLS lets ops/admin read agent-emitted events
- [ ] Error monitoring active (Sentry · Vercel Analytics · etc.)

### Backup + restore
- [ ] Supabase project backup schedule confirmed (default: daily)
- [ ] Restore process documented (test on staging at least once before launch)
- [ ] Rollback plan: how to revert a bad deploy (Vercel "Promote previous" + DB migration DOWN)

## 5. Launch sequence

```
T-7 days:  Pre-launch checklist run · staging deploy + smoke test
T-3 days:  /security-review session · address findings · re-run smoke
T-1 day:   Final staging deploy mirrors prod · take backup snapshot
T-0:       Production deploy
T+15min:   /canary-plan abort criteria check · roll back if any tripped
T+1h:      Verify all observability counters healthy · cost-budget alerts armed
T+24h:     First operational review · check audit logs · cost actuals vs estimates
T+7d:      First /drift-audit run (baseline) · /pov-gate re-run if golden dataset updated
```

## 6. Rollback runbook

### Code-only rollback (no DB change)
1. Vercel dashboard → Deployments → previous green deploy → "Promote to Production"
2. ~30 seconds to propagate
3. Update FEEDBACK-LOG.md with rollback reason

### DB migration rollback
1. Verify DOWN path in the migration's header docblock
2. `supabase db reset --linked=false` locally to validate DOWN cleanly
3. Generate inverse migration (`supabase migration new revert_<slug>`)
4. Push inverse migration
5. Then code-rollback per above

### Feature-flag-only rollback (PREFERRED · ~30s)
1. Set `<FEATURE>_ENABLED=false` in Vercel env vars
2. Redeploy current production (no code change · just env var refresh)
3. Document in FEEDBACK-LOG · investigate offline

Feature-flag rollback is the safest path · always design new features to be
disablable without code revert.

## 7. Post-launch SLA targets (customize)

| Metric | Target | Source | Alert at |
|---|---|---|---|
| P95 page load | < 2s | Vercel Analytics | > 3s for 15 min |
| API error rate | < 1% | Sentry · Vercel Logs | > 5% for 5 min |
| Database p95 query | < 200ms | Supabase dashboard | > 500ms for 10 min |
| Cost per AI call (per feature) | per COST-BUDGET.md | observability sink | > p95 × 1.5 |
| Audit log write success | > 99.9% | audit_logs INSERT count | < 99% over 1h |

